# Kid-friendly design consistency

Ages ~4–7. Match existing screens (`LaunchScreen`, `HomeScreen`, `AppShell`, letter cards) — do not invent a new visual system.

## Layout & components

- Prefer existing primitives: `AppShell`, `BigButton`, `Mascot`, `QuizGameShell`, shared modals
- Large touch targets (`h-12+`, `rounded-2xl` / `rounded-[2rem]`)
- Soft pastel / warm gradient backgrounds already used in the app — avoid flat purple-on-white AI defaults
- Visual-first: emoji/avatar, short text, one clear action per section
- Motion: light hover/tap (`active:scale-95`, small translate) — not noisy effects

## Patterns to preserve

- Profile cards: colored tiles, big emoji avatar, white border, shadow
- Games: `QuizGameShell` + mascot feedback; mid-game profile badge goes **home**, not profile switch
- Audio: import from `src/utils/audio` only (`playLetterSound`, `playWordSound`, `speakText`, `prepareAudio`) — do not fork speak/play paths per page

## Do not

- Add dashboard-style clutter, dense cards in heroes, or new design languages
- Hardcode a second audio/unlock path beside the shared facade
- Switch profiles mid-round without returning to Home (subject clears on `setProfile`)

When unsure, copy structure/spacing/classes from the nearest existing screen of the same type.
